The Katsina State government said it has finalised plans to commence screening and recruitment of graduates into the state’s  teacher’s scheme, S-Power program. The state government would also begin payment of May/June arrears and allowances for graduates of the scheme. This was contained in press statement signed by the secretary to the state government, Mustapha Muhammad Inuwa, and made available to Leadership Sunday yesterday, stating that both the screening and payment would commence on Monday , January 6, 2020, in respective centres of the  state. “Katsina State government has concluded arrangements for the screening of the NCE/ Diploma in Education holders who have applied for teaching under the state S-Power programme. “Candidates who had registered for the  programme are advised to report to their respective screening centres along with  their online registration slip, attestation form duly signed by a village or ward head and all other relevant documents. “It would be recalled that the state  committee for the recruitment of teachers under the  S-Power scheme, chaired by the SGS, Mustapha Muhammad Inuwa has called for applications to replace the 867 S- power teachers who got permanent appointment,” the statement added. Accordingly, the statement further said, “The state  S-Power committee under the chairmanship of the secretary to the government of Katsina State, Mustapha Muhammad Inuwa  is set to pay arrears of May and June, 2019 allowances to S-Power  graduates from Monday 6th to Wednesday 8th January, 2020. The payment will be made  at the 12 Zonal Quality Assurance Offices. “All affected teachers are therefore requested to report to their designated centres along with their original appointment letters and clearance forms duly signed by their reporting principal and zonal coordinator. “The 12 Zonal Quality Assurance Offices are Katsina, Rimi, Daura, Baure, Mani, Kankia, Dutsinma, Safana, Musawa, Malumfashi, Funtua, and Faskari.”